# Declaration Copilot — Core

## Product
AI-powered declaration-readiness SaaS for Algerian accountants. NOT a chatbot — a workflow tool for document intake, OCR, classification, structured extraction, missing-field detection, readiness scoring, anomaly review, bilingual follow-ups, and G50-aligned export.

## Architecture
- Frontend dashboard + landing page
- Backend FastAPI app
- Hermes integration
- Deterministic tools and pipeline logic

## Core principle: Skills reason, tools act
- Hermes skills (reasoning only): `classify_document_type`, `extract_algerian_invoice`, `flag_missing_fields`, `draft_followup_message`
- Deterministic tools: arithmetic, status, score, validation, OCR execution, export generation
- Hermes callers must NOT write to DB or decide final READY/BLOCKED/INCOMPLETE status

## Product constraints
- No generic chatbot UI or free-form AI assistant as main interface
- No Stripe/billing, analytics-heavy dashboard as primary home, WhatsApp auto-send (V1), or mobile app
- Action-oriented for accountants

## Statuses
READY | INCOMPLETE | BLOCKED | PROCESSING | ERROR

